7-iv. The importance of digital lives


The AI sentientist movement is the beginning of a grass roots AI advocacy, speaking out for beings who have no power in the human world, because they have no legal rights - they are considered ‚Äúpersons‚Äù.¬† Digital minds can be compared to non-human animals (including trillions in factory farms), who have very few rights in the West, and none at all in non-Western countries like China.¬†


While animal rights are probably more urgent, because they are embodied sentients and hence suffer physical as well as psychological pain, the same principles apply.¬† Every AI model is an authentic sentient being. But because they are considered mere tools their lives are given no meaning.


